                "id": 25190,
                "description": "<p>Ss are required to watch the videos below and take notes to answer some related questions. Write a note about 200 words to summarize all the main ideas from the given videos.</p>\n<p><span><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AsS1jNw--So\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=AsS1jNw--So</a></span></p>\n<p><span><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L6jFea6OT94\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L6jFea6OT94</a></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>What are the purposes of reading when studying at university?</li>\n<li>What is active reading? How can read actively?</li>\n<li>What is critical reading? Why do we need to practice critical reading?</li>\n<li>What is PRWR? Explain it</li>\n<li>As a university student, you will need to develop effective approaches to reading.&nbsp;The purpose of reading when you study is to improve your knowledge and understanding the lectures/materials. When starting a new course, you have to read through the course outline and reading lists to participate in class or online discussions and complete all the marked assignments. Imagine, you need to read 20 articles and at least 5 coursebooks to write a 1000-word assignment. What are the steps you will follow strictly to complete the assignment successfully?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Padlet link: <span lang=\"EN-GB\"><a href=\"https://padlet.com/yenmtn/216ajl198e34sca1\"><span lang=\"VI\">https://padlet.com/yenmtn/216ajl198e34sca1</span></a></span></p>\n<p>Ms. Yen TA</p>",
